# Finish Entry System & Limit to Current Week

We will update the `DailyEditor` to enforce that users can only add or edit entries for the current week (Monday through Friday). Historical viewing/editing will be disabled here as it will be moved elsewhere later. Additionally, we will add contextual descriptions to the entry flow categories to help clarify what goes into each section.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change will strictly limit the `DailyEditor` to **only** allow selecting dates between Monday and Friday of the **current week**. If today is a weekend, the editor will default to showing Friday's entry.

> [!NOTE]
> For the "5 day Mon to Fri" date slider, the plan is to display a row of 5 clickable day buttons (Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri) below the target date, replacing or supplementing the Left/Right arrows, to make switching days inside the week extremely quick. 

## Proposed Changes

---

### Daily Editor Flow & Restrictions

#### [MODIFY] [DailyEditor.jsx](file:///Users/mattecc/Repos/worktracker/src/components/DailyEditor/DailyEditor.jsx)
- **Current Week Calculation:** Add utility logic to compute the exact `Date` for Monday and Friday of the current week (based on the system's local time). 
- **Date Slider Update:** Replace or augment the current `< ChevronLeft /> Date < ChevronRight />` design with a 5-day (Mon-Fri) toggle/slider. Users will only be able to navigate within these 5 days.
- **Weekend Handling:** If the user opens the app on a Saturday or Sunday, default the selected date to Friday of the current week so they can still log Friday's work.
- **Descriptions:** Update the `STEPS` array to include the requested descriptions:
  - **Client Work**: `"Anything you did that goes towards your utilisation."`
  - **Practice Development**: `""` (Empty for now until defined)
  - **Business Development**: `""` (Empty for now until defined)
  - In the "flow" view, render this new description immediately under the main `What X work have you done today?` heading.

## Open Questions

> [!WARNING]  
> **Date Slider UI Design:** Currently there are large Left and Right arrows bounding the date. Would you prefer to keep the arrows but simply disable them when you hit Monday/Friday? Or would you prefer an actual row of 5 clickable Day Bubbles (Mon | Tue | Wed | Thu | Fri) under the date text to replace the arrows entirely?

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Launch the dev server and navigate to the Daily Editor.
- Verify that the date selection cannot go past the current week's Friday or before the current week's Monday.
- Verify that the "Client Work" step in the flow correctly displays the description `"Anything you did that goes towards your utilisation."`.
- Verify that the save functionality and markdown parsing works correctly for the limited dates.
